{
  "title": "The end of Roman Britain",
  "keyStage": "ks1",
  "subject": "history",
  "learningOutcome": "I can name the different groups of people living in Britain when Roman rule ended.",
  "learningCycles": [
    "Name the groups of people living in Britain when Roman rule ended.",
    "Match the groups of people to where they lived in Britain.",
    "Describe who lived in Britain after the Romans left."
  ],
  "priorKnowledge": [
    "The Romans used to rule Britain and then they left.",
    "Britain is the place where people lived in this lesson, and it can be found on a map.",
    "Some groups of people had names, such as Romans, Picts and Scots.",
    "People can live in different parts of a country.",
    "Old stories and objects can help us find out about the past."
  ],
  "keyLearningPoints": [
    "When Roman rule ended, different groups lived in Britain, including Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons.",
    "Romano-Britons lived mostly in the south and east of Britain after the Romans left.",
    "Picts lived in the north of Britain, in what is now Scotland, and Scots came from Ireland.",
    "Anglo-Saxons began to settle in parts of eastern and southern Britain after the Romans left."
  ],
  "misconceptions": [
    {
      "misconception": "All the Romans left Britain, so no people with Roman ways lived here after Roman rule ended",
      "description": "Some people stayed in Britain after the Romans left. These people are often called Romano-Britons because they lived in Britain and kept some Roman ways."
    },
    {
      "misconception": "The Scots lived in Scotland when Roman rule ended",
      "description": "At this time, the Scots came from Ireland. Some later moved to the north of Britain, and the name Scotland came later."
    },
    {
      "misconception": "The Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons all lived in the same part of Britain",
      "description": "These groups lived in different places. Pupils should use a simple map to match Picts to the north, Scots to Ireland, and Anglo-Saxons to parts of the east and south."
    }
  ],
  "keywords": [
    {
      "keyword": "Roman rule",
      "definition": "When the Romans were in charge of Britain"
    },
    {
      "keyword": "Romano-Britons",
      "definition": "People in Britain who kept some Roman ways"
    },
    {
      "keyword": "Picts",
      "definition": "A group of people who lived in the north of Britain"
    },
    {
      "keyword": "Scots",
      "definition": "A group of people who came from Ireland"
    },
    {
      "keyword": "Anglo-Saxons",
      "definition": "A group of people who settled in parts of Britain"
    }
  ],
  "starterQuiz": {
    "version": "v3",
    "questions": [
      {
        "question": "Where is Britain?",
        "hint": "It is a place you can find on a map.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "a country"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "a river",
          "a room"
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "Who used to rule Britain?",
        "hint": "These people lived a long time ago.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "Romans"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Picts",
          "Scots"
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "What happened after the Romans ruled Britain?",
        "hint": "They did not stay in Britain.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "They left Britain."
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "They built a new country.",
          "They changed its name."
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "What do we call a group of people like the Romans, Picts or Scots?",
        "hint": "They are groups of people with their own names.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "a people"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "a building",
          "a weather"
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "If people live in different parts of a country, what can this mean?",
        "hint": "Think about where people choose or are able to live.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "They live in different places."
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "They all live together.",
          "They never move home."
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "How can we find out about the past?",
        "hint": "Think about things from long ago that people can study.",
        "questionType": "multiple-choice",
        "answers": [
          "by using old objects and stories"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "by guessing every answer",
          "by looking only at new toys"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "imageMetadata": []
  },
  "cycle1": {
    "title": "Name the groups of people",
    "durationInMinutes": 8,
    "explanation": {
      "spokenExplanation": [
        "- When Roman rule ended, Britain did not become empty; different groups of people lived there.",
        "- One group was the Romano-Britons. These were people in Britain who kept some Roman ways.",
        "- Another group was the Picts. The Picts were a group of people living in Britain at this time.",
        "- Another group was the Scots. At this time, the Scots came from Ireland, so do not mix them up with the name Scotland today.",
        "- Another group was the Anglo-Saxons. They began to settle in Britain after the Romans left, so these are the four group names we need to remember: Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons."
      ],
      "accompanyingSlideDetails": "Show four simple picture cards in a row, each with a clear label: Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons. Include a small faded picture of Roman soldiers leaving Britain at the side, with a crossed arrow to show that Roman rule ended but people still lived in Britain. Keep the layout uncluttered so pupils can focus on learning and saying the four names.",
      "imagePrompt": "simple KS1 history picture cards Romano-Britons Picts Scots Anglo-Saxons Roman Britain illustration",
      "slideText": "After Roman rule ended, different groups lived in Britain. Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons."
    },
    "checkForUnderstanding": [
      {
        "question": "Which group kept some Roman ways?",
        "answers": [
          "Romano-Britons"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Anglo-Saxons",
          "Picts"
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "Which list names the four groups?",
        "answers": [
          "Anglo-Saxons, Picts, Romano-Britons, Scots"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Anglo-Saxons, Romans, Picts, Scots",
          "Picts, Romans, Romano-Britons, Scots"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "practice": "1. Say the four group names with your partner.\n2. Look at the pictures on the board.\n3. On your sheet, write each name under the right picture.\n4. Use these names: Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots, Anglo-Saxons.\n5. Then circle the name that means people kept some Roman ways.\n6. Check that you have written all four names.",
    "feedback": "Model answer\n1. The four names are Romano-Britons, Picts, Scots and Anglo-Saxons.\n2. Circle Romano-Britons.\n3. I named all four groups.\n4. I did not write Romans instead of Romano-Britons.\n5. I did not miss out Anglo-Saxons."
  },
  "cycle2": {
    "title": "Match groups to where they lived",
    "durationInMinutes": 8,
    "explanation": {
      "spokenExplanation": [
        "- We already know the four group names. Now we match each group to a place on a simple map of Britain.",
        "- Romano-Britons lived mostly in the south and east of Britain, so point to the bottom and right side of the map.",
        "- Picts lived in the north of Britain, so point to the top of the map where Scotland is now.",
        "- Scots came from Ireland, which is the island next to Britain on the left, so do not put them in Scotland yet.",
        "- Anglo-Saxons began to settle in parts of the east and south of Britain, so they match some of the same broad areas as the Romano-Britons."
      ],
      "accompanyingSlideDetails": "Show a very simple map with Britain and Ireland clearly outlined. Shade or add arrows to four broad areas: north of Britain for Picts, Ireland for Scots, south and east of Britain for Romano-Britons, and parts of the east and south for Anglo-Saxons. Use clear labels and different colours, with no extra place names except Britain, Ireland, north, east and south.",
      "imagePrompt": "simple KS1 map of Britain and Ireland showing Picts north, Scots Ireland, Romano-Britons south east, Anglo-Saxons east south",
      "slideText": "Different groups lived in different places. Use the map to match each group to where they lived."
    },
    "checkForUnderstanding": [
      {
        "question": "Who lived in the north of Britain?",
        "answers": [
          "Picts"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Scots",
          "Romans"
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "Where did the Scots come from?",
        "answers": [
          "Ireland"
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Britain",
          "Scotland"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "practice": "1. Look at the map on the worksheet.\n2. Draw lines to match each group to a place.\n3. Match Picts to the north of Britain.\n4. Match Scots to Ireland.\n5. Match Romano-Britons to the south and east.\n6. Match Anglo-Saxons to parts of the east and south.\n7. Then tell your partner one match.",
    "feedback": "Model answer\nPicts → north of Britain\nScots → Ireland\nRomano-Britons → south and east\nAnglo-Saxons → parts of the east and south\nCheck: Scots are not in Scotland here.\nCheck: Picts are in the north."
  },
  "cycle3": {
    "title": "Describe who lived in Britain",
    "durationInMinutes": 8,
    "explanation": {
      "spokenExplanation": [
        "- After the Romans left, Britain still had lots of people living in it; it was not empty.",
        "- We can describe who lived in Britain by naming the groups: Romano-Britons, Picts and Anglo-Saxons lived in Britain, and Scots came from Ireland and some later moved to the north of Britain.",
        "- Romano-Britons were people in Britain who kept some Roman ways, so some Roman ways stayed after Roman rule ended.",
        "- Picts lived in the north of Britain, and Anglo-Saxons settled in parts of the east and south.",
        "- A good history sentence tells who the people were and where they lived, for example: After the Romans left, Romano-Britons lived in the south and east, Picts lived in the north, and Anglo-Saxons settled in parts of the east and south."
      ],
      "accompanyingSlideDetails": "Show a simple map of Britain and Ireland with three clear labelled areas: north for Picts, south and east for Romano-Britons, and parts of the east and south for Anglo-Saxons. Add a small label for Scots coming from Ireland with an arrow towards the north of Britain. Alongside the map, show one short model sentence with key words highlighted: who, where. Keep the visual very clear, with large labels and limited text so pupils can use it to build spoken or written descriptions.",
      "imagePrompt": "simple KS1 map Britain Ireland Picts Romano-Britons Anglo-Saxons Scots arrow from Ireland model sentence",
      "slideText": "After the Romans left, different groups lived in and near Britain. Describe who they were and where they lived."
    },
    "checkForUnderstanding": [
      {
        "question": "Which sentence is right?",
        "answers": [
          "After the Romans left, different groups lived in Britain."
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "After the Romans left, Britain had no people living in it.",
          "After the Romans left, only Romans lived in Britain."
        ]
      },
      {
        "question": "Which sentence tells who and where?",
        "answers": [
          "Picts lived in the north of Britain."
        ],
        "distractors": [
          "Picts were a group of people.",
          "North of Britain."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "practice": "1. Use the map in the additional materials.\n2. Say one full sentence with your partner.\n3. Write 3 sentences about who lived in Britain.\n4. Use these groups: Romano-Britons, Picts, Anglo-Saxons.\n5. Tell where each group lived.\n6. You can add Scots came from Ireland.\n7. Start with: After the Romans left...\n8. Check each sentence names people and place.",
    "feedback": "Model answer\nAfter the Romans left, different groups lived in Britain.\nRomano-Britons lived in the south and east.\nPicts lived in the north of Britain.\nAnglo-Saxons settled in parts of the east and south.\nScots came from Ireland.\nCheck: each sentence names people and place."
  }
}
